Nope! Bounded channels are designed with explicit error handling in mind—pushing to a full bounded channel will result in an `Ok(None)` when using `.try_send()`. So you can write something like this:

```rust
if let Err(_) = sender.try_send(message) {
    // Handle overflow, maybe drop oldest message or queue elsewhere
}
```This gives you fine control over what happens when the channel is full.

